		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Mon, Feb 21st 2:04 PM2005 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class="sm">IP: Logged</span> | <a class="sm" href="/forum.html?forum=21&mid=1108970919146539277&post=1&replyto=1109012652247488328"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." height="11" width="17" /> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=1109012652247488328></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=295789"><span id=Scholar>oberonqa the Irrelevant</span></a><b><span id=Scholar><br>Scholar</span></b><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />801 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Good [3.96]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=oberonqa&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>Thanks guys!&nbsp;&nbsp;I'm happy to hear your getting performance increases.  As for the -notnl switch, I believe it's a leftover debugging switch.  I got the idea to use it when I saw someone in the Blizzard forums mention the switch -swtnl.  Essentially, I believe the tags break down as follows:<br><br>-notnl = No additional Texturing and Lighting (it is my belief that every texture and light source in the game has &quot;standard&quot; modes that are pre-programmed in.  By using this tag, it is my belief that you are telling the engine to use those &quot;standard&quot; modes.<br><br>-swtnl = Software Texturing and Lighting.  This switch tells the engine to handle all the textures and dynamic light sources rather than allowing the video card to do this.  I used this switch once and noticed an abysmal drop in frame rate (.01-1 FPS while wandering around forests).  I also noticed an increased CPU usage while this switch was in effect.<br><br>-hwtnl = Hardware Texturing and Lighting.  This is the default mode the engine uses and doesn't have any use.  This switch tells the engine to utilize the video card for all texturing and dynamic light sources (which is what the engine does by default).  There is no reason to use this switch and I mention it only for the sake of conversation.</p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br /><u>WoW</u><br>-<a href="HTTP://wow.allakhazam.com/profile.html?35583" target="akztarg"> <b>Neocron</b></a>: Night Elf Warrior (Durotan - Outcastz Guild)<br>-<a href="HTTP://wow.allakhazam.com/profile.html?63424" target="akztarg"> <b>Taalin</b></a>: Tauren Shamen (Shadow Council - Unguilded)<br><br><u>FFXI</u><br>-<a href="HTTP://ffxi.allakhazam.com/profile.xml?77022" target="akztarg"> <b>Neocron</b></a>: San d'Orian Tarutaru BLM60/WHM30 (Gilgamesh Server - KoruptionINC LS)&nbsp;&nbsp;(Retired)<br><br><i>Fear is the mind killer</i></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8">Posting from Somewhere.... just not sure WHERE</td></tr></table>
