		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Thu, Feb 24th 2:33 AM2005 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class="sm">IP: Logged</span> | <a class="sm" href="/forum.html?forum=21&mid=1108970919146539277&post=1&replyto=1109230359484226912"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." height="11" width="17" /> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=1109230359484226912></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=295789"><span id=Scholar>oberonqa the Irrelevant</span></a><b><span id=Scholar><br>Scholar</span></b><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />801 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Good [3.96]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=oberonqa&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>To be honest, I haven't noticed a difference in texture quality after using -notnl.&nbsp;&nbsp;I'm assuming this is because I'm running the game with the lowest possible detail settings on every possible setting (I've even tried getting the game to run at 640x480... but so far the engine has been quite stubborn about running at a minimum of 800x600).<br><br>But yea... TnL is a major bottleneck.  Even if your running a modern card which handles TnL, a slow system can negate whatever performance gains having a modern card provides due to the card being forced to run at the same speed as a combination of the CPU and the bus (basically.. if your card can handle 3 billion polygons per second but your processor can only handle 1 billion polygons per second and can only send/receive 500,000 polygons per second down the bus to/from the card, your card is effectively operating at 500,000 polygons per second).  This of course isn't even taking into consideration the speed of the memory chips and the rate of transfer of data from the hard drive to memory.</p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br /><u>WoW</u><br>-<a href="HTTP://wow.allakhazam.com/profile.html?35583" target="akztarg"> <b>Neocron</b></a>: Night Elf Warrior (Durotan - Outcastz Guild)<br>-<a href="HTTP://wow.allakhazam.com/profile.html?63424" target="akztarg"> <b>Taalin</b></a>: Tauren Shamen (Shadow Council - Unguilded)<br><br><u>FFXI</u><br>-<a href="HTTP://ffxi.allakhazam.com/profile.xml?77022" target="akztarg"> <b>Neocron</b></a>: San d'Orian Tarutaru BLM60/WHM30 (Gilgamesh Server - KoruptionINC LS)&nbsp;&nbsp;(Retired)<br><br><i>Fear is the mind killer</i></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8">Posting from Somewhere.... just not sure WHERE</td></tr></table>
